OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F317A1781568171
OL,3,CFifa urged to investigate World Cup
OL,4,Cofficial over 'white power' gesture
OL,6,F"Why is a VAR supervisor using this
OL,7,Fsymbol at a global football event at
OL,8,Fthe very moment he knows the cameras
OL,9,Fare on him?" Fare continued
OL,11,FThe gesture was previously popularised
OL,12,Fby children as the "circle game",
OL,13,Fwhere someone flashes an upside-down
OL,14,Fokay sign below their waist and anyone
OL,15,Fwho looks at it is caught out and
OL,16,Fpunched in the shoulder.
OL,18,FIt was then appropriated as a signal
OL,19,Ffor white supremacy a decade ago,
OL,20,Fstarting as a hoax on the far-right
OL,21,Fonline message board 4chan.
OL,26,@nD@AOUqD@LO]
